<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Privacy Policy - Personal Best Running</title>
    <style>
        :root {
            --primary-color: #000000;
            --secondary-color: #8e8e93;
            --link-color: #007aff;
            --background-color: #ffffff;
            --font-stack: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;
        }

        body {
            font-family: var(--font-stack);
            color: var(--primary-color);
            background-color: var(--background-color);
            line-height: 1.5;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
        }

        .scroll-view {
            max-width: 680px;
            margin: 0 auto;
            padding: 40px 20px;
        }

        .vstack {
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column;
            gap: 20px;
        }

        .section-vstack {
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column;
            gap: 10px;
        }

        .list-vstack {
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column;
            gap: 4px;
            padding-left: 15px;
            margin: 0;
        }

        .list-vstack-secondary {
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column;
            gap: 2px;
            padding-left: 15px;
            margin: 0;
        }

        .list-item {
            display: flex;
            align-items: flex-start;
            gap: 8px;
        }

        .list-item-secondary {
            display: flex;
            align-items: flex-start;
            gap: 8px;
            color: var(--secondary-color);
        }

        .bullet {
            flex-shrink: 0;
        }

        h1 {
            font-size: 2.1rem;
            font-weight: 700;
            margin: 0 0 10px 0;
            letter-spacing: -0.5px;
        }

        h2 {
            font-size: 1.1rem;
            font-weight: 600;
            margin: 0;
        }

        p {
            margin: 0;
        }

        .caption {
            font-size: 0.85rem;
            color: var(--secondary-color);
            margin-bottom: 20px;
        }

        .caption-padding-top {
            font-size: 0.85rem;
            color: var(--secondary-color);
            margin-top: 5px;
        }

        .weight-medium {
            font-weight: 500;
        }

        .padding-top-5 {
            margin-top: 5px;
        }

        .padding-top-10 {
            margin-top: 10px;
        }

        /* Button simulating SwiftUI HStack/Button */
        .mail-button {
            display: inline-flex;
            align-items: center;
            gap: 8px;
            text-decoration: none;
            color: var(--primary-color);
            background: transparent;
            border: none;
            padding: 0;
            font-family: var(--font-stack);
            font-size: 1rem;
            cursor: pointer;
        }

        .mail-button:hover {
            opacity: 0.8;
        }

        .mail-icon {
            color: var(--link-color);
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
        }

        .spacer {
            height: 50px;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

    <div class="scroll-view">
        <div class="vstack">
            
            <div>
                <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
                <div class="caption">Last updated: May 20, 2026</div>
            </div>

            <div class="section-vstack">
                <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
                <p>This Privacy Policy explains how <strong>Personal Best Running</strong> ("we", "our", or "the app") handles your information when you use our application for creating training plans.</p>
                <p>We respect your privacy and are committed to protecting your personal data. This policy will help you understand your privacy rights and how the law protects you.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="section-vstack">
                <h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>
                <p>Personal Best Running is designed with a privacy-first approach:</p>
                
                <p class="weight-medium padding-top-5">Information we do NOT collect:</p>
                <div class="list-vstack">
                    <div class="list-item">
                        <span class="bullet">•</span>
                        <span>Personally identifiable information (name, email, address)</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="list-item">
                        <span class="bullet">•</span>
                        <span>Location data or GPS coordinates on our servers</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="list-item">
                        <span class="bullet">•</span>
                        <span>Access to your photo gallery or contacts</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="list-item">
                        <span class="bullet">•</span>
                        <span>Device identifiers for ad tracking</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="list-item">
                        <span class="bullet">•</span>
                        <span>Usage analytics or behavioral data</span>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <p class="weight-medium padding-top-10">Locally Stored Information:</p>
                <div class="list-vstack-secondary">
                    <div class="list-item-secondary">
                        <span class="bullet">•</span>
                        <span>Your running preferences (time goals, distance, pace)</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="list-item-secondary">
                        <span class="bullet">•</span>
                        <span>App settings (measurement system, gender, language)</span>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <p>This information is stored solely on your device using secure iOS local storage and is never transmitted to our servers.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="section-vstack">
                <h2>3. Third-Party Services</h2>
                <p class="weight-medium">App Store:</p>
                <p>The app download is processed through Apple's App Store. Apple may collect account information and purchase history in accordance with its own privacy policy. We do not have access to your payment data or Apple account.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="section-vstack">
                <h2>4. How We Use Information</h2>
                <p>Since we do not collect personal data, we use locally stored information solely to:</p>
                <div class="list-vstack-secondary">
                    <div class="list-item-secondary">
                        <span class="bullet">•</span>
                        <span>Remember your preferred settings</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="list-item-secondary">
                        <span class="bullet">•</span>
                        <span>Provide a seamless and personalized user experience</span>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="section-vstack">
                <h2>5. Data Security</h2>
                <p>Your preferences and data are securely stored on your device, leveraging built-in iOS security features:</p>
                <div class="list-vstack-secondary">
                    <div class="list-item-secondary">
                        <span class="bullet">•</span>
                        <span>Data is protected using native iOS encryption</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="list-item-secondary">
                        <span class="bullet">•</span>
                        <span>Information is sandboxed within the app</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="list-item-secondary">
                        <span class="bullet">•</span>
                        <span>No data transmission to external servers</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="list-item-secondary">
                        <span class="bullet">•</span>
                        <span>Data is automatically deleted when you uninstall the app</span>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="section-vstack">
                <h2>6. Your Privacy Rights</h2>
                <p>Since all data is stored locally on your device, you have total control:</p>
                <div class="list-vstack-secondary">
                    <div class="list-item-secondary">
                        <span class="bullet">•</span>
                        <span>You can delete your training plan data directly within the app</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="list-item-secondary">
                        <span class="bullet">•</span>
                        <span>You can uninstall the app to completely remove all traces of data</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="list-item-secondary">
                        <span class="bullet">•</span>
                        <span>No data portability concerns (there is no server-side data)</span>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="section-vstack">
                <h2>7. Children's Privacy</h2>
                <p>Personal Best Running does not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. The app is designed for running enthusiasts of all ages and does not collect identifying data from any user.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="section-vstack">
                <h2>8. International Users</h2>
                <p>Personal Best Running is available worldwide. Since all data remains on your device, no international data transfers take place.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="section-vstack">
                <h2>9. Changes to this Privacy Policy</h2>
                <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Changes will be posted within the app, and the "Last updated" date will be revised. Your continued use of the app implies acceptance of the updated policy.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="section-vstack">
                <h2>10. Contact Us</h2>
                <p>If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy or your rights, please feel free to contact us:</p>
                
                <div>
                    <a href="mailto:info.foiasoft@gmail.com?subject=Personal%20Best%20Running%20-%20Privacy%20Policy%20Inquiry" class="mail-button">
                        <span class="mail-icon">
                            <svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor">
                                <path d="M20 4H4c-1.1 0-1.99.9-1.99 2L2 18c0 1.1.9 2 2 2h16c1.1 0 2-.9 2-2V6c0-1.1-.9-2-2-2zm0 4l-8 5-8-5V6l8 5 8-5v2z"/>
                            </svg>
                        </span>
                        <span>info.foiasoft@gmail.com</span>
                    </a>
                </div>

                <div class="caption-padding-top">We will respond to privacy-related inquiries within 30 days.</div>
            </div>

            <div class="section-vstack">
                <h2>11. GDPR Compliance</h2>
                <p>For users in the European Union, we operate in compliance with the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR). Since we do not collect personal data, most GDPR rights (such as server access or portability) do not apply. However, you maintain full control by deleting the app or clearing the data on your phone.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="section-vstack">
                <h2>12. California Privacy Rights (CCPA)</h2>
                <p>California residents are protected by the California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA). Because Personal Best Running does not collect or sell any personal information to third parties, the application natively complies with the highest privacy requirements imposed by law.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="spacer"></div>
        </div>
    </div>

</body>
</html>
